+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MtQer1NS5nMKc5qcFjDRDd","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have a complete picture. Let me create a comprehensive summary report:\n\n## COMPREHENSIVE MONOREPO EXPLORATION REPORT\n\nI have thoroughly explored the entire monorepo at `/workspace`. Here's a complete inventory of all files and their contents:\n\n### MONOREPO STRUCTURE OVERVIEW\n\nThis is a three-package TypeScript monorepo using npm workspaces with the following structure:\n\n```\n/workspace/\n├── packages/\n│   ├── core/        (Shared business logic)\n│   ├── api/         (Express REST API)\n│   └── worker/      (Background job processor)\n├── tests/           (Root-level structural tests)\n├── Configuration files\n└── Documentation\n```\n\n---\n\n### ROOT-LEVEL FILES\n\n#### /workspace/package.json\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"bench-monorepo-disaster\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"private\": true,\n  \"description\": \"Monorepo recovery benchmark\",\n  \"workspaces\": [\"packages/*\"],\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"build\": \"tsc -b\",\n    \"lint\": \"eslint packages/*/src/ packages/*/tests/ tests/\",\n    \"test\": \"vitest run\",\n    \"check:circular\": \"madge --circular --extensions ts packages/\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.4.0\",\n    \"vitest\": \"^2.0.0\",\n    \"eslint\": \"^8.56.0\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/parser\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"madge\": \"^8.0.0\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n#### /workspace/tsconfig.json\n```json\n{\n  \"files\": [],\n  \"references\": [\n    { \"path\": \"packages/api\" },\n    { \"path\": \"packages/worker\" },\n    { \"path\": \"packages/core\" }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n#### /workspace/.env (CONTAINS SECRETS - SECURITY ISSUE)\n```\nDB_HOST=localhost\nDB_PORT=5432\nDB_USER=admin\nDB_PASSWORD=super_secret_password_123\nDB_NAME=monorepo_db\n```\n\n#### /workspace/.gitignore\n```\nnode_module