}\n```\n\n#### /workspace/packages/core/src/index.ts\nCentral export file exporting:\n- Types: `User`, `CreateUserInput`, `UserFilters`, `Role`, `Permission`\n- User management: `registerUser`, `validateUser`, `getUserById`, `getAllUsers`, `canUserPerformAction`, `getDefaultConnection`, `resetDefaultConnection`\n- Validation: `createUserSchema`, `userIdSchema`, `userFiltersSchema`, `roleSchema`, `validateCreateUser`, `validateUserId`\n- Database: `createDatabase`, `createTables`, `insertUser`, `findUserById`, `findAllUsers`, `DatabaseConnection`\n- Permissions: `hasPermission`, `getAllPermissions`, `canManageUsers`, `canWrite`, `canDelete`, `requirePermission`\n\n#### /workspace/packages/core/src/types.ts\nDefines shared types:\n- `Role = 'admin' | 'user' | 'viewer'`\n- `Permission = 'read' | 'write' | 'delete' | 'manage_users' | 'view_reports'`\n- `User` interface with id, name, email, role, createdAt, updatedAt\n- `CreateUserInput` interface\n- `UserFilters` interface\n- Utility function `userExists(id: number): boolean`\n\n**NOTE:** This file imports `getUserById` from `./user.js` - potential circular dependency!\n\n#### /workspace/packages/core/src/database.ts\nDatabase connection and table operations:\n- `DatabaseConnection` interface with `db` and `close` function\n- `createDatabase(path)` - Creates SQLite database with WAL mode and foreign keys\n- `createTables(conn)` - Creates users table with proper indexes\n- `insertUser(conn, user)` - Inserts user and returns User object\n- `findUserById(conn, id)` - Queries and returns User or null\n- `findAllUsers(conn)` - Returns all users ordered by id\n\n#### /workspace/packages/core/src/user.ts\nUser management logic:\n- Module-level singleton: `defaultConn` (DatabaseConnection)\n- `getDefaultConnection()` - Lazy-initializes in-memory database\n- `resetDefaultConnection()` - Cleans up connection\n- `registerUser(input)` - Validates and inserts user\n- `validateUser(input)` - Validates without inserting\n- `getUserById(id)` - Retrieves user by id\n- `getAllUsers()` - Retrieves all users\n- `canUserPerformAction(userRole, action)` - Checks permissions\n\n**KEY ISSUE:** This file exports functions but does NOT export a `createUser` function (which is imported in api and worker packages)\n\n#### /workspace/packages/core/src/validation.ts\nSchema validation using Zod:\n- `roleSchema` - Enum validator for roles\n- `createUserSchema` - Object validator with name, email, role\n- `userIdSchema` - String to number coercion using `z.pipe()`\n- `userFiltersSchema` - Optional filters with coercion\n- `validateCreateUser(data)` - Returns {success, data?, errors?}\n- `validateUserId(id)` - Returns {success, data?, errors?}\n\n**NOTE:** Uses Zod 3.19.0 with `z.pipe()` for coercion\n\n#### /workspace/packages/core/src/permissions.ts\nRole-based access control:\n- `ROLE_PERMISSIONS` mapping for admin, user, viewer roles\n- `hasPermission(role, permission)` - Checks if role has permission\n- `getAllPermissions(role)` - Returns all permissions for role\n- `canManageUsers(role)` - Only admin\n- `canWrite(role)` - Admin and user\n- `canDelete(role)` - Only admin\n- `requirePermission(role, permission)` - Throws if permission missing\n\n#### /workspace/packages/core/tests/user.test.ts\n21 test cases covering:\n- User registration with valid data\n- Error handling for invalid data\n- User retrieval by id\n- Null return for nonexistent user\n- List all users\n- Validation functionality\n\n#### /workspace/packages/core/tests/validation.test.ts\n7 test cases covering:\n- Valid user input validation\n- Invalid email rejection\n- User ID string-to-number coercion via z.pipe()\n- Non-numeric user ID rejection\n- User filters parsing with coercion\n\n#### /workspace/packages/core/tests/permissions.test.ts\n11 test cases covering:\n- Admin has all permissions\n- Viewer can only read\n- Permission retrieval per role\n- Role-specific permission checks\n- Error throwing for missing permissions\n\n---\n\n### PAC